            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "mAh stands for milliampere-hours — a unit measuring how much electrical charge a battery can store. A 10,000mAh power bank can theoretically deliver 10,000 milliamps (10 amps) for one hour, or 1,000 milliamps for 10 hours. However, the rated mAh is measured at the internal battery voltage of 3.7V, while USB output requires 5V — this voltage conversion results in 30-40% loss, meaning usable capacity is typically 60-70% of the rated number."
